data.value: Set Quality Control Parameters. QAB-F101 Values Are The Official Settings However At Low Infeed Speed A Minimum Temperature of 170 C Results in RED Moisture Values . The Simplified Setting Adjusts For This.

data.name: Label21.Text
data.value: PID is a control loop equation used to reach and maintain a temperature. Firstly the SetPoint (SP) and Temperature (PV) is measured. The Equation then compares Temperature (PV) to the SetPoint (SP) and generates an error value (E). The value is examined with one or more of the three proportional, integral, and derivative methodologies. As a result, the equation alters the control variable Flame (CV) to correct the Error (E).
